summary: In this context, ethylbenzene and 2-butene are both identified as volatile organic compounds (VOCs) present in the emissions from municipal solid waste (MSW) biostabilization. Ethylbenzene is categorized as an alkylated benzene, while 2-butene is classified as an alkene. However, there is no direct interaction or specific relationship discussed between these two compounds beyond their classification as VOCs emitted during the same process.
